The five accused in the murder of Senzo Meyiwa are making their second appearance at the Boksburg Magistrate's court BOKSBURG - Five men accused of Senzo Meyiwa's murder are back in court on Friday. Meyiwa was gunned down in 2014 at the house of his then songstress girlfriend, Kelly Khumalo. READ: Senzo Meyiwa murder: Expect another arrest soon, says Nel At their first appearance, four of the five denied involvement in the murder of the late Orlando Pirates and Bafana Bafana goalkeeper. They claim they are being used as scapegoats and even refused to enter the dock. The Meyiwa family says it wants justice to be served